 <section class="card" id="11">
                <img src="Images/Oily_Skin_Care_2.JPG" alt="oily skin">  
                 <div>
                    <h3>About Oily Skin</h3> 
                
    <p>
       Oily skin is one of the most common skin types, especially in hot and humid weather, and it usually happens when the skin produces excess sebum (natural oil). Although oil is important to keep the skin protected and moisturized, too much oil can cause many problems like acne, pimples, blackheads, whiteheads, and a shiny appearance.
        
        <span id="dots1">...</span>
        
        <span id="more1" class="more-text" style="display:none;">
           The good thing is that oily skin can be managed easily with the right skincare routine and healthy habits. The first and most important skincare tip for oily skin is cleansing properly. People with oily skin should wash their face twice a day, once in the morning and once at night, using a gentle gel-based cleanser. Cleansing removes extra oil, dirt, and bacteria from the skin and helps prevent clogged pores. However, washing the face too many times is not good because it can strip natural oils and cause the skin to produce even more oil. Another important tip is to use toner, which can help control oil production and reduce the appearance of large pores. Toners with ingredients like niacinamide, witch hazel, or salicylic acid work well for oily skin, but alcohol-based toners should be avoided because they can irritate the skin. Moisturizing is another step that many oily skin people skip, but it is actually very important.Even oily skin needs moisture, because when skin becomes dry, it produces more oil to protect itself. Therefore, using a lightweight, oil-free, and non-comedogenic moisturizer helps keep the skin balanced, soft, and hydrated without making it greasy. Sunscreen is also a must for oily skin because sun exposure can cause tanning, pigmentation, dark spots, and early aging. Many people think sunscreen makes the face more oily, but nowadays there are many gel-based and matte sunscreens specially made for oily skin. Using SPF 30 or SPF 50 sunscreen daily protects the skin from harmful UV rays and keeps the skin tone even. Another useful tip is exfoliating the skin one or two times a week. Exfoliation removes dead skin cells and helps clean clogged pores, which reduces blackheads and pimples. Chemical exfoliants like salicylic acid (BHA) are best for oily skin because they penetrate deep into the pores and remove excess oil. However, exfoliating too much can damage the skin barrier and cause irritation, so it should be done carefully. Using a clay mask once a week is also very beneficial for oily skin because clay absorbs extra oil, removes dirt, and deeply cleans pores. Natural masks like multani mitti are very popular and effective for oily skin. Another important skincare tip is to avoid touching the face again and again because hands carry bacteria and dirt which can spread to the face and cause pimples. People with oily skin should also avoid using heavy makeup or thick creams because these products can block pores and increase acne. It is always better to use non-comedogenic and oil-free makeup products that do not clog pores. During the day, if the face becomes too oily, instead of washing the face repeatedly, it is better to use blotting paper or a tissue to gently remove excess oil. This helps reduce shine without disturbing the skin’s natural balance. Diet and lifestyle also play a big role in controlling oily skin. Drinking enough water keeps the skin hydrated from inside and helps remove toxins from the body. Eating healthy foods like fruits, vegetables, and nuts improves skin health, while oily junk food, too much sugar, and fried items can increase oil production and cause acne breakouts. Stress and lack of sleep can also trigger hormonal imbalance which increases oil and pimples, so getting proper sleep and staying relaxed is very important. Another helpful tip is to use serums with ingredients like niacinamide, salicylic acid, or tea tree because these ingredients control oil, reduce acne, and improve skin texture. Retinol can also be useful for oily skin because it helps prevent clogged pores and reduces acne marks, but it should be used carefully and only at night. In conclusion, oily skin is not a problem if you follow the right skincare routine and maintain healthy habits. The best skincare tips for oily skin include washing the face twice daily, using oil-free moisturizer, applying sunscreen daily, exfoliating weekly, using clay masks, avoiding heavy products, and eating healthy food. Consistency is the key because skincare results take time, but with regular care, oily skin can become balanced, clear, and healthy.
        </span>
    </p>

